    <edge source=" manage down the numbers of transitions, there really should be no excuse not to get transitions right, then.&#10;Speaker: Dawn Bowden AM&#10;Content: Okay, thank you. Thank you, Chair.&#10;Speaker: Lynne Neagle AM&#10;Content: Okay. We've got some really important questions now about legacy, because throughout the session this morning you've referred to ongoing work, really, and that is a major concern for the committee. Suzy Davies.&#10;Speaker: Suzy Davies AM&#10;Content: Yes, thank you, Chair, we are a little bit worried that this programme is coming to an end in a matter of months when perhaps its work's not been completed. Obviously, we've got the Welsh Government's strategy for mental health running until 2022, which is a few years longer. Can you tell me whether you think your programme needs to continue, perhaps even if it's just for the same length of time as Together for Mental Health, or is its work done and it needs to be picked up now by a different system?&#10;Speaker: Carol Shillabeer&#10;Content: Thank you for that. Can I just say, I've given this so much thought over the time, because I think you might have asked me" target="The integration of psychological therapies into a social care unit in south Wales could lead to more fluid roles moving across sectors, as well as the design of fully integrated services. This is one test of the seamless health and social care system for Wales, with the goal of bringing these sectors together over the next five to ten years. The emphasis on this being a whole-system approach to children and young people's mental health is crucial, as any imbalance in the system could jeopardize progress. Specifically, the programme aims to make earlier progress on psychological therapies, recognizing the need for greater support, particularly for looked-after children who have experienced challenging backgrounds. This focus on emotional health and mental health is a key part of health assessments for these young people. The aim is to ensure that this work reaches children in various situations, including those who are fostered and may not have frequent looked-after children reviews.">
