;&#10;The impact on the ground includes:&#10;&#10;1. Increased coordination between different groups working for the benefit of children in care.&#10;2. More integrated services, breaking down traditional sector boundaries.&#10;3. Improved access to psychological therapies and support for children.&#10;4. A focus on earlier intervention and prevention, rather than just dealing with issues when they reach a crisis point.&#10;5. Potential challenges in implementing more fluid roles and fully integrated services, but also an opportunity to address these issues as they arise.">
