    <edge source="1. The transcript discusses plans to create a more integrated and joined-up approach between health and social care for approximately 100 children who have experienced care in multiple settings. This initiative aims to bring together social care and healthcare teams, which currently operate separately, to provide better coordinated services for these vulnerable children.&#10;2. To further this goal, a meeting with the Children's Commissioner is scheduled for 9 July. The purpose of this meeting is to explore this potential collaboration and discuss next steps in developing joined-up teams to support these children effectively. This aligns with the broader aim of the Together for Children and Young People program to improve outcomes for vulnerable children and young people in Wales." target="1. Develop values-led approaches: A commitment is made to create and implement values-led strategies that will bring multiple agencies together, ensuring a common purpose in addressing early help and enhanced support. This approach aims to foster collaboration and unity among different organizations working towards the same goals.&#10;&#10;2. Determine ingredients for successful working: The second commitment involves developing the essential elements or &quot;ingredients&quot; necessary for effective collaboration in this area. By identifying and focusing on these key components, agencies can work together more successfully and provide better support to those who need it.&#10;&#10;3. Propose priorities and sequencing of next steps: The third commitment focuses on determining the priorities and sequence of actions moving forward. This step will help agencies plan their efforts effectively by understanding which areas require immediate attention and how to approach them in a logical order, ensuring that resources are used efficiently and progress is made systematically.">
